  "prompt": "Which laptop is the best one to buy for gaming under 35000?",
  "response": "Finding a good gaming laptop under INR 35,000 can be quite challenging, as gaming laptops generally require powerful hardware, which typically costs more. However, you can look for laptops that offer the best possible performance within this budget. Here are some tips and options that might be suitable for light gaming or older games:\n\n1. **AMD Ryzen Processors**: Look for laptops with AMD Ryzen 3 or Ryzen 5 processors as they often come with integrated Vega graphics, which are relatively better for gaming compared to Intel's integrated graphics.\n\n2. **8GB RAM**: Ensure that the laptop has at least 8GB of RAM, as this is important for both gaming and general performance.\n\n3. **Dual Storage Options**: While SSDs are preferable for faster load times, having at least a combination of SSD and HDD can offer speed with larger storage capacity.\n\nHere are a few models that might fit the criteria, although availability and specific configurations can vary:\n\n- **HP 15s Series**: Often found with Ryzen 3 processors, which are adequate for light gaming.\n- **Lenovo Ideapad**: Models with Ryzen 3 processors are another option, with decent build quality and performance.\n- **Acer Aspire Series**: Look for models with Ryzen processors, as they tend to offer good value for money.\n\nPlease note that these laptops are suitable for light gaming and older games. If you want to play more demanding titles, you may need to increase your budget or consider a desktop PC, which might offer better performance for your money in this price range. Always check the specs carefully and read user reviews to ensure the laptop meets your expectations.",
